checkers.regex

Class RegexUtil

  • @Nullable java.lang.Object
    • checkers.regex.RegexUtil

  • public class RegexUtil
extends @Nullable Object
    Utility methods for regular expressions.

    For an example of intended use, see section Testing whether a string is a regular expression in the Checker Framework manual.

    Runtime Dependency: Using this class introduces a runtime dependency. This means that you need to distribute (or link to) the Checker Framework, along with your binaries. To eliminate this dependency, you can simply copy this class into your own project.

      • asRegex

        public static @Nullable String asRegex(@Nullable String s)
        Returns the argument as a @Regex String if it is a regex, otherwise throws an error. The purpose of this method is to suppress Regex Checker warnings. Once the the Regex Checker supports flow-sensitivity, it should be very rarely needed.

      • asRegex

        Returns the argument as a @Regex(groups) String if it is a regex with at least the given number of groups, otherwise throws an error. The purpose of this method is to suppress Regex Checker warnings. Once the the Regex Checker supports flow-sensitivity, it should be very rarely needed.
